11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
13 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 160.41 of Title 17, unless there
14 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
15 A. As used in this section:
16 1. “Commercial solar energy facility” means an installation of
17 interconnected photovoltaic, ground-mounted solar panels on a tract
18 of land in this state, which generate electricity for distribution.
19 Provided, the term shall not include any solar energy generated
20 through distributed generation installed by residential customers;
21 and
22 2. “Distributed generation” means distributed generation as
23 defined in Section 156 of Title 17 of the Oklahoma Statutes.
24
